OL,3,CMartyn's Law laid before parliament
OL,5,FIn response to today's development, Ms
OL,6,FMurray commended the speed at which
OL,7,Fthe new government has moved to help
OL,8,Fmake Martyn's Law a reality.
OL,10,F"He said he would act quickly and he
OL,11,Fhas", she said.
OL,13,F"Today means we are one step closer to
OL,14,Fmaking public spaces safer for
OL,15,Feveryone. It is also hugely important
OL,16,Ffor my family that Martyn's Law will
OL,17,Fbe on the statute book ahead of the
OL,18,Fnext anniversary of Martyn's death."
OL,20,FFigen Murray OBE gives her reaction to
OL,21,Fthe latest development
